<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="O" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Overcome" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Overcome</orth> (cf. <emph>O'ercome</emph>) 1) to come or pass over: <cit><quote>can such things be and o. us like a summer's cloud,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 3.4.111" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. III, 4, 111</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) to overpower, to conquer: <bibl n="shak. ven 891" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 891</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ven 891" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 891</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lll 4.1.74" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 1, 74</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.3.7" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 3, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.4.27" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B V, 4, 27</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.3.100" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 3, 100</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.1.187" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 1, 187</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 3.5.71" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. III, 5, 71</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 3.2.177" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. III, 2, 177</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 5.5.56" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 56</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 2.2.72" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. II, 2, 72</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 5.1.156" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 156</bibl> (Ff <emph>o'ercame</emph>).
<lb />3) intr. to be victorious: <bibl n="shak. lll 4.1.70" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 1, 70</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.1.70" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 1, 70</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lll 4.1.70" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 1, 70</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ayl 5.2.35" default="NO" valid="yes">As V, 2, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.3.46" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 3, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.1.107" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 1, 107</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.1.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 1, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 1.4.70" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 4, 70</bibl>.
